42116 1 Indicates
whether to
enable the quick
startup function
after the power
grid is recovered
from short-term
interruption. If it
is set to 0, the
power grid is
disabled. That is,
the power grid is
still connected
according to the
normal startup
process after the
power grid is
interrupted for a
short time. If it is
set to 1, the
power is
enabled. After
the power grid
recovers from
short-term
interruption, the
quick startup
process is
followed. Some
detection items
are skipped.
