6.3.6 Reading Device /Êì²Ēàä (0x2B)
This command code allows reading ²nì²fiàä and added packets that are relevant
to the physical and function description of the remote devices.
Simulate the interface of the read device ²nì²fià as an address space. This
address space consists of a set of addressable data elements. The data elements
are objects to be read, and the object IDs determine these data elements.
A data element consists of three objects:
1. Basic device ²nì²fiàǿ All objects of this type are mandatory, such as the
vendor name, product code, and revision version.
2. Normal device ²nì²fiàǿ Except basic data objects, the device provides
additional and optional ²nì²fiàä and data object description. fin all
types of objects according to fin²ì²Ñnä in the standard, but the execution of
this type of objects is optional.
3. Extended device ²nì²fiàǿ In addition to the normal data objects, the device
provides additional and optional ²nì²fiàä and special data object
description. All the data is related to the device.
